    "millsfield:images_texts": [
      "1934\nTHE S-42 WAS DESIGNED AND BUILT FOR PAN AMERICAN. CLEANER LINES THAN\nTHE S-40,\nTHE S-40, THE S-42 SHORTENED THE TIME TO BUENOS AIRES AND ALSO WAS\nUSED TO SURVEY PAA'S PACIFIC ROUTES. IN JULY, 1937, A S-42 FLYING\nBOAT MADE THE FIRST REGULAR AIRLINE CROSSING OF THE NORTH ATLANTIC\nOCEAN STARTING FROM THE UNITED STATES, FLYING FIRST TO ENGLAND BY THE\nNORTHERN ROUTE, AND THEN TO PORTUGAL BY THE BERMUDA-AZORES ROUTE. THE\nSEE SI CLIPPER CARRIED 32 PASSENGERS IN LUXURIOUS COMPARTMENTS"
    ],
